# Zod validation

Every Server Action and every Route Handler validates input with Zod before reading any field. No exceptions.

## Schema location

Per feature:

```
src/features/billing/
  schemas/
    start-subscription.schema.ts
  actions/
    start-subscription.action.ts
```

The schema file exports:

```ts
// src/features/billing/schemas/start-subscription.schema.ts
import { z } from "zod";

export const startSubscriptionSchema = z.object({
  priceCode: z.enum(["VIP_ANNUAL", "BUSINESS_ANNUAL"]),
  turnstileToken: z.string().min(20).max(4096),
});

export type StartSubscriptionInput = z.infer<typeof startSubscriptionSchema>;
```

## Action shape

```ts
// src/features/billing/actions/start-subscription.action.ts
"use server";
import "server-only";
import { startSubscriptionSchema } from "../schemas/start-subscription.schema";
import { verifyTurnstile } from "@/lib/captcha/turnstile";
import { ratelimitServerAction } from "@/lib/rate-limit/server-action";
import { getCurrentUserOrThrow } from "@/lib/auth/current-user";

export type StartSubscriptionResult =
  | { ok: true; checkoutUrl: string }
  | { ok: false; error: "RATE_LIMITED" | "INVALID_CAPTCHA" | "VALIDATION_FAILED" | "INTERNAL" };

export async function startSubscription(
  raw: unknown,
): Promise<StartSubscriptionResult> {
  // 1. Parse first — fail before any side effect.
  const parsed = startSubscriptionSchema.safeParse(raw);
  if (!parsed.success) return { ok: false, error: "VALIDATION_FAILED" };

  // 2. Auth.
  const user = await getCurrentUserOrThrow();

  // 3. Rate limit + Turnstile.
  const rl = await ratelimitServerAction.limit(user.id);
  if (!rl.success) return { ok: false, error: "RATE_LIMITED" };
  const cap = await verifyTurnstile(parsed.data.turnstileToken);
  if (!cap.ok) return { ok: false, error: "INVALID_CAPTCHA" };

  // 4. Business logic.
  try {
    const checkoutUrl = await createCheckoutSession({ user, ... });
    return { ok: true, checkoutUrl };
  } catch (e) {
    // log + return generic error (never leak to client)
    return { ok: false, error: "INTERNAL" };
  }
}
```

## Why `Result<T, E>` instead of throwing

- Throwing in Server Actions ends up in `error.tsx` boundaries and gives the user a generic error page. We want field-level feedback.
- `safeParse` already returns a `Result`. Stay in that style end-to-end.
- The discriminated union is exhaustively matchable on the client: `if (!res.ok) switch (res.error) { ... }`.

## What to validate

Not just shape, but also:

- Length bounds (`.min(1).max(500)` on free-text).
- Enum membership (`z.enum([...])` for status / type values).
- Format (`.email()`, `.url()`, `.uuid()`).
- Cross-field invariants (`.refine(...)` for "if A then B").

## Errors mapped to i18n keys, not strings

On the client:

```tsx
const messages: Record<typeof res.error, string> = {
  RATE_LIMITED: t("errors.rateLimited"),
  INVALID_CAPTCHA: t("errors.invalidCaptcha"),
  VALIDATION_FAILED: t("errors.validationFailed"),
  INTERNAL: t("errors.internal"),
};
```

Never `toast(res.error)` directly — that ships the raw enum value to users.

